item.description:
Recently i downloaded some lectures from youtube in m4a format. My hardware portable player doesn&rsquo;t support it so I converted files like this:
ffmpeg -i file.m4a -acodec libvorbis -aq 4 -vn -ac 2 -map_metadata 0 file.ogg Complete script is:
#!/bin/bash # Author: Simon Legner &lt;Simon.Legner@gmail.com&gt; convert () { in=&#34;$1&#34; out=&#34;${in%.m4a}.ogg&#34; ffmpeg -i &#34;$in&#34; \ -acodec libvorbis -aq 4 -vn -ac 2 \ -map_metadata 0 \ &#34;$out&#34; } if [[ $# == 0 ]]; then echo Converts m4a files to Ogg Vorbis using ffmpeg.
